Etymology: The species is named after Prof. Dr. Indra Jaya, Dean of the Faculty of Fisheries and Marine Sciences (
2007–2011
), Bogor Agricultural University, Indonesia , who supported the second author during his guest lectureship at IPB .

Description: Based on 20 whole-mount preparations. Measurements and ratios in
Table 1
. Body elongate, widest in mid-body, tapering anteriorly and posteriorly (
Figure 3
);
7 specimens
found with anterior extremity withdrawn (
Figure 4
). Tegument spinous; spines squamous, tiny, reach to posterior extremity. Rhynchus broader anteriorly, aperture ventral; hood smooth. Mouth just anterior to ovary, at about mid-body. Pharynx globular. Caecum oval, mostly posteriorly to pharynx.
